<paragraph id="8BA036829D31A25365DA9A86FA2EF84F" blockId="7.[151,1436,1902,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis id="B96BEA909D31A25365DA9A86FD90F872" bold="true" box="[199,546,1974,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="184">Occurrence and distribution.</emphasis>
In the present study, this species occurs in the southernmost part of the Eastern region of the Brazilian continental shelf, around Cabo Frio (
<figureCitation id="13242A079D31A253667E9AEAFC1CF84E" box="[867,942,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1403,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of Xestoleberis species in Brazilian continental shelf. The hatched area corresponds to the Transitional Zone of Coimbra et al. (1995). Each dot represents one sample." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239626/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="184">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD724A59D31A25366809AEBFC1CF84E" box="[925,942,2011,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="184" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
; Tab. 
<number id="3DD724A59D31A25366E69AEBFBB5F84E" box="[1019,1031,2011,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="184" value="1.0">1</number>
) at a depth range of 
<quantity id="4CE79B679D31A25360139AEAFA2AF84F" box="[1294,1432,2010,2035]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.45" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="184" unit="m" value="64.5" valueMax="94.0" valueMin="35.0">
35 to 
<specimenCount id="9D19FD0B9D31A25360459AEBFA2AF84F" box="[1368,1432,2011,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="184" type="generic">94 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
